\par \hich\af0\dbch\af4\loch\f0 In this format, it makes sense to play for random ante. The top card from your deck is your ante. Look at it, show it to your opponents, and then put it aside (poss\hich\af0\dbch\af4\loch\f0 
ibly leaving you with a 39 card deck, that's OK). 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af4\loch\f0 "But what if I lose cards that I need and that my opponent doesn't want?" The biggest problem with random ante is that every card lost is a card you need and every card gained is not. But this is a tradin
\hich\af0\dbch\af4\loch\f0 g league. If you lose your Disintegrator Ray to someone without Quislings or Pharaohs in their deck, trade for it back. 
\par 
